  abstract = {The proceedings contain 45 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Smart Homes, Smart Urban Spaces and New Assistive Living Space Concepts in the Smart City. The topics include: Multi-resident location tracking in smart home through non-wearable unobtrusive sensors; people tracking in ambient assisted living environments using low-cost thermal image cameras; a preprocessing algorithm to increase OCR performance on application processor-centric FPGA architectures; deep learning-based food image recognition for computer-aided dietary assessment; deep learning based emotion recognition from chinese speech; SVM based predictive model for SGA detection; situation-aware decision making in smart homes; towards an adaptation model for smart homes; design and implementation of a prototype system for automatic obstacle avoidance information collection vehicle; an empirical study of the design space of smart home routers; simplifying installation and maintenance of ambient intelligent solutions toward large scale deployment; a distributed VCG-like multi-resource allocation algorithm for multimedia systems; an ADL recognition system on smart phone; a scalable clinical intelligent decision support system; gaining insights in designing tools to support low-sodium diet; design and implementation of fall detection system using MPU6050 arduino; modeling the in-home lifestyle of chronic anorectal patients via a sensing home; evaluation framework for smart technology mental health interventions; an exploratory investigation into the relationship between willingness-to-adopt mobile devices and shopping experience; an infrastructure-free swimmer localization system based on smartphone sensors and supporting referential gestures in mobile remote presence. \copyright{} 2016 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
