  abstract = {The proceedings contain 31 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Innovation in Medicine and Healthcare. The topics include: An informative mhealth app for healthcare and weight control; information and communication technologies, and the positive mental health in the seniors; prediction and prevention of addictions through the implementation of a computational social simulator; CFD simulation of the oral-nasal flow partitioning during a breathing cycle based on the soft palate movement; neural network backpropagation with applications into nutrition; automatic and robust vessel segmentation in CT volumes using submodular constrained graph; a study of nuclei classification methods in histopathological images; semi-automatic segmentation of paranasal sinuses from CT images using active contour with group similarity constraints; the possibility of hemorheological parameters as precursors of recurrent strokes; simulation technologies supporting collaborative training for emergency medical services personnel; an indentation-type instrument for measuring soft tissue elasticity; detection of liver tumor candidates from CT images using deep convolutional neural networks; computerized features for LI-RADS based computer-aided diagnosis of liver lesions; improving measurement accuracy for rheumatoid arthritis medical examinations; design and implementation of a social networking service-based application for supporting disaster medical assistance teams; quantitative assessment of small bowel motility using cine MR sequence images and superpixels; template-matching based tracking of cervical spines in videofluorography during swallowing and multimodal imaging of the breast to retrieve the reference state in the absence of gravity using finite element modeling. \copyright{} 2017 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
