  abstract = {A telemedicine system has been devised to alleviate the health disparities resulting from the imbalance of nutrition in various countries, age groups, and social environments. For the elderly and children who have difficulties ingesting pills, liquid medication was remotely controlled and printed using the Internet of Things (IoT)-enabled 3D printers. As a result of the convergence of single line design (SLD) and piston type extrusion (PTE), non-Newtonian fluid resulted in a printing time reduction of up to 12\%, depending on the viscosity of the material and the curvature of the shape. The PTE process used materials with viscosity ranging from 0.1-10 Pa{$\bullet$}s, and the discharge was four times as accurate as that of the target discharge amount of \textpm{} 6.1\% with SLD. \copyright{} 2020 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
