  abstract = {Purpose: This study aimed to create and assess machine learning (ML) models that utilize nutritional and inflammatory indices, focusing on the advanced lung cancer inflammation index (ALI) and neutrophil-to-albumin ratio (NAR), to improve the prediction accuracy of PE prognosis. Patients and methods: We conducted a retrospective analysis of 312 patients, comprising 254 survivors and 58 non-survivors. The Boruta algorithm was used to identify significant variables, and four ML models (XGBoost, Random Forest, Logistic Regression, and SVM) were employed to analyze the clinical data and assess the performance of the models. Results: The XGBoost model, with optimal hyperparameters, achieved the best performance, with an accuracy of 0.882, an F1-score of 0.889, a precision of 0.917, a sensitivity of 0.863, a specificity of 0.905, and an AUC of 0.873. Analysis of feature importance indicated that the most critical predictors across models were respiratory failure, log-transformed ALI, albumin level, age, diastolic blood pressure, and NAR. Conclusion: The ML-based prediction models effectively predicted the prognosis of PE, with the XGBoost model exhibiting good performance. Respiratory failure, ALI, albumin level, age, diastolic blood pressure, and NAR were correlated with PE prognosis. \copyright{} 2024 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
  langid = {english},
  keywords = {adult,Adult,Advanced Lung Cancer Inflammation Index,aged,Aged,albumin,Albumin,algorithm,Algorithm,area under the curve,Area Under The Curve,Article,blood,Blood,blood pressure,Blood Pressure,body mass,Body Mass,cerebrovascular accident,Cerebrovascular Accident,computer assisted tomography,Computer Assisted Tomography,diabetes mellitus,Diabetes Mellitus,diagnosis,Diagnosis,diagnostic test accuracy study,Diagnostic Test Accuracy Study,diastolic blood pressure,Diastolic Blood Pressure,dyspnea,Dyspnea,faintness,Faintness,female,Female,follow up,Follow Up,health care system,Health Care System,human,Human,Humans,hypertension,Hypertension,inflammation,Inflammation,logistic regression analysis,Logistic Regression Analysis,lung angiography,Lung Angiography,lung cancer,Lung Cancer,lung cancer inflammation index,Lung Cancer Inflammation Index,lung embolism,Lung Embolism,machine learning,Machine Learning,major clinical study,Major Clinical Study,male,Male,middle aged,Middle Aged,neutrophil,Neutrophil,neutrophil count,Neutrophil Count,neutrophil lymphocyte ratio,Neutrophil Lymphocyte Ratio,neutrophil to albumin ratio,Neutrophil To Albumin Ratio,Neutrophil-to-albumin Ratio,nutrition,Nutrition,pneumonia,Pneumonia,prediction,Prediction,prognosis,Prognosis,Pulmonary Embolism,R Software Version 4.3.2,random forest,Random Forest,receiver operating characteristic,Receiver Operating Characteristic,respiratory failure,Respiratory Failure,Retrospective Studies,retrospective study,Retrospective Study,risk factor,Risk Factor,sensitivity and specificity,Sensitivity And Specificity,support vector machine,Support Vector Machine,systolic blood pressure,Systolic Blood Pressure,thorax pain,Thorax Pain}
