  abstract = {The proceedings contain 15 papers. The topics discussed include: combining the benefits of CCA and SVMs for SSVEP-based BCIs in real-world conditions; artificial intelligence in XPRIZE DeepQ tricorder; denoising of joint tracking data by Kinect sensors using clustered Gaussian process regression; research challenges of emerging technologies supporting life-long health and wellbeing; gamification of heel raise plantar-flexion physiotherapy; empirical mode decomposition of throat microphone recordings for intake classification; wearable emotion recognition system based on GSR and PPG signals; live personalized nutrition recommendation engine; managing family healthcare with multimedia chat apps: a survey on what is missing; toward personalized treatment of chronic diseases - the CKDCase study; DeepQ arrhythmia database: a large-scale dataset for arrhythmia detector evaluation; exploring challenges in automated just-in-time adaptive food choice interventions; elderly people living alone: detecting home visits with ambient and wearable sensing; few-shot learning using a small-sized dataset of high-resolution FUNDUS images for glaucoma diagnosis; and MedFit: a mobile application for patients in CVD recovery. \copyright{} 2017 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
