  publisher = {{Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.}},
  doi = {10.1109/ICTC.2018.8539441},
  abstract = {The Philippine Conditional Cash Transfer (CCT) of the Philippines has started since 2007. This Philippine government program and human development measure provides conditional cash grants to the poorest of the poor, to improve the health, nutrition, and the education of children aged 0-18. This study provides a framework of state-of-the-art visualization tool in presenting data that provides significant reports that will aid government decision making that involves poor Filipino families. With the vast rising of technology and never-ending growth of government data in the Philippines, it is a big possibility that the data generated by the tool can give solutions and amendments to future management policies and improves administration tasks. This research shows a framework for the development of a web application of a decision support system to support the National Advisory Committee (NAC) and NAC Technical Working Group (NAC-TWG) of the Department of Social Welfare and Development of the Philippines. The data analyses reports produced on this interactive data visualization tool can be used as a basis for program and action recommendation of government offices. The framework includes descriptive and diagnostic analysis after data cleansing and simulation. It also features forecasting and prediction functionalities. \copyright{} 2019 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
  isbn = {9781538650400 (ISBN)},
