  abstract = {Background: This study explores the potential of Artificial Intelligence (AI)-generated social media influencers to disseminate cancer prevention messages. Utilizing a Generative AI (GenAI) application, we created a virtual persona, "Wanda", to promote cancer awareness on Instagram. Methods: We created five posts, addressing the five most modifiable risk factors for cancer: tobacco consumption, unhealthy diet, sun exposure, alcohol consumption, and Human Papillomavirus (HPV) infection. To amplify the campaign's reach, posts were boosted using a custom-targeted as well as an automated advertisement algorithm. An overall budget of \texteuro 100 was equally distributed between the two algorithms. Campaign performance was assessed based on the number of users reached and the age distribution of the audience. Results: The campaign achieved a total of 9902 recognitions, with a cost-efficiency analysis revealing an average expenditure of \texteuro 0.013 per reach. The most economical intervention achieved a cost of only \texteuro 0.006 per reach. In comparing the two advertisement strategies, we observed similar overall reach but noted differences in the age demographics of the audience. Conclusion: Our findings underscore the potential of combining generative AI with strategically targeted advertisement to promote cancer prevention messages effectively, with minimal time and financial investment. We discuss chances presented by GenAI applications in health communication, their implication, and the impact of parasocial relationships on content perception. This study highlights the potential of AI-driven influencers as scalable tools for digital health communication. \copyright{} 2025 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
  langid = {english},
  keywords = {adolescent,Adolescent,adult,Adult,age distribution,Age Distribution,aged,Aged,Ai-generated Influencers,alcohol consumption,Alcohol Consumption,Article,artificial intelligence,Artificial Intelligence,attitude to health,Attitude To Health,cancer prevention,Cancer Prevention,cost benefit analysis,Cost Benefit Analysis,Cost-benefit Analysis,Cost-Benefit Analysis,demographics,Demographics,Digital Health Campaigns,economics,Economics,female,Female,Genai,generative artificial intelligence,Generative Artificial Intelligence,health care cost,Health Care Cost,Health Communication,Health Knowledge Attitudes Practice,health promotion,Health Promotion,human,Human,Humans,male,Male,middle aged,Middle Aged,neoplasm,Neoplasm,Neoplasms,papillomavirus infection,Papillomavirus Infection,prevention and control,Prevention And Control,procedures,Procedures,risk factor,Risk Factor,Risk Factors,Risk Groups,social media,Social Media,social media influencer,Social Media Influencer,sun exposure,Sun Exposure,Targeted Prevention,tobacco consumption,Tobacco Consumption,unhealthy diet,Unhealthy Diet,young adult,Young Adult}
